e fueling social conflicts that arise from desperation as life-sustaining conditions erode.In a book of extraordinary scope, Nixon examines a cluster of writer-activists affiliated with the environmentalism of the poor in the global South. By approaching environmental justice literature from this transnational perspective, he exposes the limitations of the national and local frames that dominate environmental writing. And by skillfully illuminating the strategies these writer-activists deploy to give dramatic visibility to environmental emergencies, Nixon invites his readers to engage with some of the most pressing challenges of our time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2011z978311026123308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET SCIENCE TECHNOLOGY AND MEDICINE 2011z9783110261202oZDB-23-DMN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013 (Canada)z978311075606708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220540uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067406119440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674061194423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674061194.jpg  a978-3-11-026123-3  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2011b2011  a978-3-11-044220-5  Harvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-075606-7  HUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013 (Canada)b2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  